1
00:00:02,358 --> 00:00:04,225
♪

2
00:00:05,746 --> 00:00:08,179
♪

3
00:01:06,356 --> 00:01:08,506
♪

4
00:01:12,812 --> 00:01:16,058
SUPERMAN [NARRATING]: <i>A black hole. A collapsed star so dense</i>

5
00:01:16,082 --> 00:01:19,651
<i>that not even light can escape from its gravitational pull.</i>

6
00:01:22,873 --> 00:01:25,034
<i>S.T.A.R. Labs had discovered one</i>

7
00:01:25,058 --> 00:01:27,437
<i>less than six light years from Earth.</i>

8
00:01:27,461 --> 00:01:28,671
<i>And with my ship,</i>

9
00:01:28,695 --> 00:01:30,940
<i>we had the perfect opportunity to study it,</i>

10
00:01:30,964 --> 00:01:32,447
<i>up close and personal.</i>

11
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:49,459
<i>After watching the probe being pulled into the gravity well,</i>

12
00:01:49,483 --> 00:01:52,045
<i>this was about as up close as I wanted to get.</i>

13
00:01:52,069 --> 00:01:54,464
<i>But I wasn't the only one observing it.</i>

14
00:01:54,488 --> 00:01:56,037
[ALARM BEEPING]

15
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,100
[ALL SCREAMING]

16
00:02:10,203 --> 00:02:11,764
[ALL GRUNTING]

17
00:02:11,788 --> 00:02:14,767
<i>I had no idea how their ship got so far off course,</i>

18
00:02:14,791 --> 00:02:17,075
<i>but I didn't have much time.</i>

19
00:02:18,044 --> 00:02:20,011
♪

20
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,902
[GRUNTING]

21
00:02:47,924 --> 00:02:50,091
[GRUNTING]

22
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,950
<i>They were going to be all right.</i>

23
00:03:04,974 --> 00:03:06,870
<i>Still, I had to find a place to take them.</i>

24
00:03:06,894 --> 00:03:10,445
<i>Fortunately, their ship had left a vapor trail.</i>

25
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:15,711
<i>It led to a nearby star system</i>

26
00:03:15,735 --> 00:03:17,997
<i>and one planet in particular.</i>

27
00:03:18,021 --> 00:03:20,421
♪

28
00:03:40,961 --> 00:03:42,693
[ALL GROANING]

29
00:03:44,548 --> 00:03:46,164
[DOOR OPENING]

30
00:03:49,602 --> 00:03:51,030
I hope everyone's all right.

31
00:03:51,054 --> 00:03:52,749
[ALL GASP]

32
00:03:52,773 --> 00:03:53,917
He's one of them.

33
00:03:53,941 --> 00:03:54,918
Excuse me?

34
00:03:54,942 --> 00:03:56,169
WOMAN: What should we do?

35
00:03:56,193 --> 00:03:58,103
MAN [WHISPERING]: I don't know. Let's go.

36
00:03:58,127 --> 00:04:00,173
What's wrong?

37
00:04:00,197 --> 00:04:01,613
Run!

38
00:04:02,616 --> 00:04:03,982
♪

39
00:04:05,652 --> 00:04:07,013
I don't understand.

40
00:04:07,037 --> 00:04:08,431
I just saved your lives.

41
00:04:08,455 --> 00:04:10,433
Then maybe you'd better run too.

42
00:04:10,457 --> 00:04:12,290
[GRUNTING]

43
00:04:15,545 --> 00:04:17,262
So much for gratitude.

44
00:04:25,389 --> 00:04:26,754
[YELLS]

45
00:04:31,895 --> 00:04:34,841
He's still alive. I think he's one of them.

46
00:04:34,865 --> 00:04:36,642
MAN [OVER RADIO]: <i>That's not our concern.</i>

47
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:38,833
<i>Our orders are to take them all out.</i>

48
00:04:51,047 --> 00:04:52,047
[GRUNTS]

49
00:05:16,857 --> 00:05:18,556
[YELLS]

50
00:05:31,988 --> 00:05:35,173
Maybe you can tell me why I'm so popular around here.

51
00:05:37,127 --> 00:05:39,143
[SHIPS APPROACHING]

52
00:05:49,256 --> 00:05:51,322
[GUNS COCKING]

53
00:05:53,326 --> 00:05:54,570
Hold your fire!

54
00:05:54,594 --> 00:05:56,989
Stand down at once!

55
00:05:57,013 --> 00:06:00,225
Kal-El, welcome to New Krypton.

56
00:06:00,249 --> 00:06:02,350
♪

57
00:06:19,727 --> 00:06:22,490
You'll find the food almost as good as on Krypton,

58
00:06:22,514 --> 00:06:25,298
if you can remember that far back.

59
00:06:27,301 --> 00:06:28,301
Ah!

60
00:06:29,387 --> 00:06:31,254
Idiot.

61
00:06:34,859 --> 00:06:38,756
I see you still have a weakness for the inferior, Kal-El.

62
00:06:38,780 --> 00:06:40,541
Some things never change.

63
00:06:40,565 --> 00:06:42,009
The last time I saw you,

64
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:43,661
you were trapped in the Phantom Zone.

65
00:06:43,685 --> 00:06:44,695
How did...?

66
00:06:44,719 --> 00:06:47,197
Did we escape? A stroke of luck.

67
00:06:47,221 --> 00:06:49,466
About a year ago, scientists here

68
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:51,802
<i>detected two meteors of lunar proportions</i>

69
00:06:51,826 --> 00:06:53,821
<i>heading towards the black hole.</i>

70
00:06:53,845 --> 00:06:57,013
<i>They sent out a research ship to study the phenomenon.</i>

71
00:07:01,836 --> 00:07:03,302
[ALL GRUNTING]

72
00:07:05,056 --> 00:07:07,017
<i>When the meteors collided,</i>

73
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:10,359
<i>the released energy tore open a rift into the Phantom Zone.</i>

74
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,363
[GASPING]

75
00:07:28,963 --> 00:07:30,730
JAX-UR: <i>We were free, but helpless.</i>

76
00:07:33,117 --> 00:07:36,029
<i>Had the aliens not been there, we would have asphyxiated</i>

77
00:07:36,053 --> 00:07:38,265
<i>or been pulled into the hole.</i>

78
00:07:38,289 --> 00:07:40,055
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

79
00:07:42,043 --> 00:07:43,921
And to express your gratitude,

80
00:07:43,945 --> 00:07:45,589
you seized control of their planet.

81
00:07:45,613 --> 00:07:48,359
You see things so crudely, Kal-El.

82
00:07:48,383 --> 00:07:51,579
ALTERUS: General Jax-Ur, your pardon.

83
00:07:51,603 --> 00:07:52,780
What is it?

84
00:07:52,804 --> 00:07:55,499
Four of the escapees have been recaptured.

85
00:07:55,523 --> 00:07:56,951
Two are still at large.

86
00:07:56,975 --> 00:07:59,736
JAX-UR: Come back when you have them all.

87
00:08:02,730 --> 00:08:06,393
Those citizens you so recklessly saved were criminals.

88
00:08:06,417 --> 00:08:09,163
Anarchists, condemned by due process.

89
00:08:09,187 --> 00:08:12,371
Even on your world, you don't interfere with that, do you?

90
00:08:15,610 --> 00:08:18,305
Before we arrived, this was a planet in chaos,

91
00:08:18,329 --> 00:08:20,925
divided by petty conflicts and factions,

92
00:08:20,949 --> 00:08:22,409
not unlike Earth.

93
00:08:22,433 --> 00:08:24,962
We have brought to it the order it needed.

94
00:08:24,986 --> 00:08:26,564
Is that a fact?

95
00:08:26,588 --> 00:08:30,401
Don't take my word for it. See for yourself, Kal-El.

96
00:08:30,425 --> 00:08:32,425
♪

97
00:08:37,014 --> 00:08:39,643
Production instead of destruction.

98
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:44,582
Factories, where there were once useless forests and wetlands.

99
00:08:44,606 --> 00:08:49,136
JAX-UR: <i>Workers who now cooperate with each other, instead of compete.</i>

100
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:54,458
<i>A job for everyone according to his abilities and our needs.</i>

101
00:08:54,482 --> 00:08:56,415
[GRUNTING]

102
00:09:05,093 --> 00:09:07,871
<i>To insure a future as orderly as the present,</i>

103
00:09:07,895 --> 00:09:11,609
<i>we have built new schools to teach morality, loyalty</i>

104
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,243
<i>and purpose.</i>

105
00:09:13,267 --> 00:09:17,213
<i>Needless to say, disciplinary problems are now nonexistent.</i>

106
00:09:17,237 --> 00:09:18,621
[ALARM BEEPING]

107
00:09:25,546 --> 00:09:26,990
<i>All over this planet,</i>

108
00:09:27,014 --> 00:09:29,009
<i>we are tearing down the irrational past</i>

109
00:09:29,033 --> 00:09:32,129
<i>in order to make room for an efficient future.</i>

110
00:09:32,153 --> 00:09:35,082
In one year, we have put a new face on this world,

111
00:09:35,106 --> 00:09:38,719
creating the paradise Krypton would have been under our rule.

112
00:09:38,743 --> 00:09:41,222
Now, if only someone down there would smile.

113
00:09:41,246 --> 00:09:44,308
I hope you're not thinking of opposing us, Kal-El.

114
00:09:44,332 --> 00:09:46,877
We've had a year to develop our powers.

115
00:09:46,901 --> 00:09:49,146
I don't think we have to worry about that, Mala.

116
00:09:49,170 --> 00:09:51,648
Kal-El knows his place, and this planet

117
00:09:51,672 --> 00:09:53,901
is simply out of his jurisdiction.

118
00:09:53,925 --> 00:09:55,524
[MISSILE APPROACHING]

119
00:10:08,939 --> 00:10:10,789
I'll find them.

120
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:13,787
Anarchists.

121
00:10:13,811 --> 00:10:16,629
These days, a minor annoyance.

122
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:21,767
♪

123
00:10:32,496 --> 00:10:34,691
I've had my troopers recover your ship.

124
00:10:34,715 --> 00:10:36,093
You'll find it undamaged,

125
00:10:36,117 --> 00:10:38,395
though I'm sure you'll want to x-ray it yourself.

126
00:10:38,419 --> 00:10:41,115
I know I would.

127
00:10:41,139 --> 00:10:43,372
Have a pleasant journey.

128
00:10:54,101 --> 00:10:55,600
[GRUNTS]

129
00:10:57,638 --> 00:10:59,099
You're taking quite a risk.

130
00:10:59,123 --> 00:11:00,935
How do you know I won't turn you in?

131
00:11:00,959 --> 00:11:02,603
It's a chance I'll have to take.

132
00:11:02,627 --> 00:11:04,438
My name is Cetea.

133
00:11:04,462 --> 00:11:06,357
I used to work for the National Council.

134
00:11:06,381 --> 00:11:08,826
The people you saved in the execution ship were leaders,

135
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:09,944
not criminals.

136
00:11:09,968 --> 00:11:11,695
We may have our wars and factions,

137
00:11:11,719 --> 00:11:14,281
but we are not the barbarians Jax-Ur portrays.

138
00:11:14,305 --> 00:11:16,951
Even so, I can't fight him, Cetea.

139
00:11:16,975 --> 00:11:19,703
You must. You're the only one powerful enough.

140
00:11:19,727 --> 00:11:22,539
If I do, your planet will be the loser.

141
00:11:22,563 --> 00:11:26,410
A battle between us would cause more destruction and bloodshed

142
00:11:26,434 --> 00:11:28,528
than all the wars that came before.

143
00:11:28,552 --> 00:11:30,096
We're willing to risk it.

144
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,466
I'm not. Not that way.

145
00:11:32,490 --> 00:11:35,586
I understand. This is not your world.

146
00:11:35,610 --> 00:11:37,621
But I don't believe our royal benefactors

147
00:11:37,645 --> 00:11:39,139
have given you the whole picture.

148
00:11:39,163 --> 00:11:42,064
There's something else you should see.

149
00:11:44,419 --> 00:11:46,897
From what I gather, he was unconscious for about an hour.

150
00:11:46,921 --> 00:11:48,248
Cetea!

151
00:11:48,272 --> 00:11:51,685
We should have killed her the first time she crossed us.

152
00:11:51,709 --> 00:11:56,345
She doesn't know much, but still, we'd better find them.

153
00:11:57,515 --> 00:11:59,693
You have performed well, Alterus.

154
00:11:59,717 --> 00:12:03,413
As you always do.

155
00:12:03,437 --> 00:12:05,954
Business before pleasure, Mala.

156
00:12:13,197 --> 00:12:14,529
Ugh.

157
00:12:28,112 --> 00:12:29,623
This is what they didn't show you

158
00:12:29,647 --> 00:12:30,796
on your little tour.

159
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:49,743
Interstellar ships, manned by robots.

160
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:52,368
They're building an armada.

161
00:13:02,780 --> 00:13:03,823
[BUTTONS BEEPING]

162
00:13:03,847 --> 00:13:04,924
What are you doing?

163
00:13:04,948 --> 00:13:06,593
Activating the guidance system.

164
00:13:06,617 --> 00:13:08,617
I wanna know where these ships are headed.

165
00:13:11,322 --> 00:13:12,421
Here.

166
00:13:15,960 --> 00:13:18,193
Earth.

167
00:13:19,130 --> 00:13:20,741
Why am I not surprised?

168
00:13:20,765 --> 00:13:22,609
[ALARM BEEPING]

169
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:23,944
They know we're here.

170
00:13:23,968 --> 00:13:25,935
♪

171
00:13:44,288 --> 00:13:45,988
JAX-UR: Fall back.

172
00:13:46,957 --> 00:13:49,592
Well done, Kal-El.

173
00:13:55,916 --> 00:13:57,082
[GRUNTING]

174
00:14:04,058 --> 00:14:06,503
The restraints create a magnetic field

175
00:14:06,527 --> 00:14:08,110
not even you can break.

176
00:14:11,015 --> 00:14:14,366
You should have left when you had the chance, Kal-El.

177
00:14:15,219 --> 00:14:16,318
Ha!

178
00:14:30,624 --> 00:14:32,519
JAX-UR: Mesmerizing.

179
00:14:32,543 --> 00:14:34,320
Of all the phenomena of nature,

180
00:14:34,344 --> 00:14:37,473
none fascinates me more than a black hole.

181
00:14:37,497 --> 00:14:41,210
It is the one true force of absolute power.

182
00:14:41,234 --> 00:14:44,269
Everything it touches becomes its own.

183
00:14:47,508 --> 00:14:48,923
You would admire that.

184
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,660
We're within range, Jax-Ur.

185
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:54,490
Think of it, Kal-El.

186
00:14:54,514 --> 00:14:56,359
You might actually last long enough

187
00:14:56,383 --> 00:14:58,494
to get a glimpse inside the hole.

188
00:14:58,518 --> 00:15:00,614
I almost envy you.

189
00:15:00,638 --> 00:15:02,054
Almost.

190
00:15:02,856 --> 00:15:04,038
Ah!

191
00:15:06,093 --> 00:15:08,504
Great Ral!

192
00:15:08,528 --> 00:15:10,156
Alterus, what's happening?

193
00:15:10,180 --> 00:15:12,324
We've hit a gravitational anomaly.

194
00:15:12,348 --> 00:15:13,660
Navigation is off-course.

195
00:15:13,684 --> 00:15:14,961
We're being pulled into it.

196
00:15:14,985 --> 00:15:17,664
Keep an eye on them while we adjust the navigation.

197
00:15:17,688 --> 00:15:19,154
Come.

198
00:15:20,724 --> 00:15:23,124
A short reprieve at best, Kal-El.

199
00:15:24,778 --> 00:15:26,305
♪

200
00:15:26,329 --> 00:15:27,424
Plague on you

201
00:15:27,448 --> 00:15:30,260
and your self-serving treachery, Alterus.

202
00:15:30,284 --> 00:15:34,502
My dear Cetea, I deserve much worse than that.

203
00:15:39,025 --> 00:15:41,704
We have to hurry. It won't take that witch long to realize

204
00:15:41,728 --> 00:15:43,544
it was I who disabled the navigation.

205
00:15:45,165 --> 00:15:46,743
JAX-UR: Look for yourself, Mala.

206
00:15:46,767 --> 00:15:48,784
There's no anomaly here.

207
00:15:50,354 --> 00:15:53,032
Your soldier boy has been playing tricks.

208
00:15:53,056 --> 00:15:54,084
[ALARM BEEPING]

209
00:15:54,108 --> 00:15:55,301
What's that?

210
00:15:55,325 --> 00:15:56,419
An escape pod.

211
00:15:56,443 --> 00:15:58,576
♪

212
00:16:01,615 --> 00:16:03,760
It's ejected with two passengers.

213
00:16:03,784 --> 00:16:05,250
Two?

214
00:16:07,421 --> 00:16:09,182
I decided to stick around.

215
00:16:09,206 --> 00:16:11,768
I thought we might find a new planet.

216
00:16:11,792 --> 00:16:14,759
A nice, cozy one, just for the two of you.

217
00:16:20,217 --> 00:16:22,479
[BOTH GRUNTING]

218
00:16:22,503 --> 00:16:25,120
I mean it, you're not going back.

219
00:16:33,296 --> 00:16:34,528
[GRUNTS]

220
00:16:40,370 --> 00:16:41,886
Ah!

221
00:16:44,158 --> 00:16:46,557
We're caught in the gravity well!

222
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:54,733
[BOTH GRUNTING]

223
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:07,762
JAX-UR: Mala!

224
00:17:08,515 --> 00:17:10,131
Put it on.

225
00:17:20,527 --> 00:17:22,026
[GRUNTING]

226
00:17:34,324 --> 00:17:36,202
[GRUNTING]

227
00:17:36,226 --> 00:17:37,959
Ah!

228
00:17:39,997 --> 00:17:41,829
[GASPING]

229
00:17:45,169 --> 00:17:47,702
Your lungs are going to burn.

230
00:17:52,309 --> 00:17:54,442
[GROANING]

231
00:17:56,146 --> 00:17:59,014
Forget Kal-El. He'll never survive without air.

232
00:18:20,087 --> 00:18:21,886
[BOTH GASP]

233
00:18:49,449 --> 00:18:51,199
[SCREAMING]

234
00:18:52,569 --> 00:18:54,336
[SCREAMING]

235
00:19:06,499 --> 00:19:09,200
♪

236
00:19:24,217 --> 00:19:27,463
SUPERMAN [NARRATING]: <i>Although Cetea's people were grateful for my help,</i>

237
00:19:27,487 --> 00:19:30,216
<i>I wondered if it wasn't I who should be grateful.</i>

238
00:19:30,240 --> 00:19:32,418
<i>They reminded me of the saying,</i>

239
00:19:32,442 --> 00:19:35,838
<i>"Evil triumphs when good men do nothing."</i>

240
00:19:35,862 --> 00:19:38,896
<i>I won't forget it again.</i>

241
00:19:42,777 --> 00:19:45,027
♪

